## Required Context Files

**Lost? Read [`.ai/START_HERE.md`](.ai/START_HERE.md) first.**

**Free-text entry:** don't know which skill to run? Invoke `@ai-director - <what you want>` (Agent OS), `@ui-director` (`.ai.ui`), `@biz-director` (`.ai.biz`), `@soc-director` (`.ai.soc`), or `@x-director` for cross-framework work.

### Frameworks registry (cross-framework discovery)

Sister frameworks are siblings on disk; `.ai/` is this framework. Paths resolve at runtime — a `REPLACE:*` or empty cell means "auto-discover".

| Framework | Director | Path | Bootstrap artifact |
|-----------|----------|------|--------------------|
| `.ai` (Agent OS) | `@ai-director` | *this directory* | `.ai/skills/README.md` |
| `.ai.ui` (UI Design OS) | `@ui-director` | `/mnt/work/Projects/.ai.ui` | `.ai.ui/skills/README.md` |
| `.ai.biz` (Business OS) | `@biz-director` | `/mnt/work/Projects/.ai.biz` | `.ai.biz/skills/README.md` |
| `.ai.soc` (Social OS) | `@soc-director` | `/mnt/work/Projects/.ai.soc` | `.ai.soc/skills/README.md` |

**Path resolution:** (1) use a filled path cell; `REPLACE:*`/empty → fall through. (2) Auto-discover: fat-client parent = `$REPO_ROOT/.ai/..`; thin-client parent = `$AGENT_OS_SOURCE/..`; check `${parent}/.ai.ui|.ai.biz|.ai.soc`; missing = "not installed". (3) Before routing, verify the framework dir + its `skills/README.md` exist; if absent, route to `@ai-director` prefixed `[degraded: <framework> not installed]` — never route into the void.

### Source resolution — fat-client vs thin-client (MANDATORY before reading any `.ai/...` path)

**Agent OS source (thin-client only — set by `@deploy-basic`):**

AGENT_OS_SOURCE=/mnt/work/Projects/.ai

*(Still `REPLACE_BASICSOURCE` → this repo is fat-client.)*

| Mode | Bootstrapped via | Framework assets | `AGENT_OS_SOURCE` |
|------|------------------|------------------|-------------------|
| **Fat-client** (vendored) | `@deploy-files` / `@project-bootstrap init` | this repo's `.ai/` | unset (token unchanged) |
| **Thin-client** (remote) | `@deploy-basic` | the source Agent OS; this repo holds only `.cursorrules` + `.work/` | absolute path |

**Rule (apply before reading any `.ai/...` reference):**
1. `.cursorrules` + `.work/**` — always read locally, both modes.
2. **Thin-client** (`AGENT_OS_SOURCE` set + readable): read every other `.ai/<path>` from `$AGENT_OS_SOURCE/<path>` (skills, standards, concepts, docs, scripts, templates, READMEs). Any `.ai/<x>` referenced anywhere — inside a skill document, or inside this `.cursorrules` file itself — resolves to `$AGENT_OS_SOURCE/<x>`.
3. **Fat-client** (token unset/unchanged): read `.ai/<path>` locally.
4. App code + `.work/...` resolve locally in both modes.
5. **Thin-client + unreachable source:** stop and report `agent-os source unreachable: $AGENT_OS_SOURCE` — do not fall back or guess.

**Executable script paths are pre-resolved, not left to interpretation.** The `bash /mnt/work/Projects/.ai/scripts/...` commands below (Change-safety gate table, Co-authored-by hook install) are rewritten to the absolute `$AGENT_OS_SOURCE/scripts/...` path by `@deploy-basic` at bootstrap/`update` time — do not re-derive them at read-time. If a thin-client `.cursorrules` still shows literal `/mnt/work/Projects/.ai/scripts/...` text, it predates this rewrite; run `@deploy-basic update` to re-bake it.

**First thin-client bootstrap** (no local skill yet): run from source (`@deploy-basic - /abs/target`) or invoke the shell from target (`bash /abs/source/scripts/deploy-basic.sh .`). Afterward the source pointer lets the local agent load every skill from source.

