## Skills

Skills live under `.ai/skills/<id>/skill.md` (folder name = id). When a task matches a skill's purpose, read its `skill.md` and follow it. Tool-agnostic (Cursor, Claude Code, Codex, opencode).

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| plan-foundation | P0–P6 orchestration; certify plan-master-ready |
| plan-master | Master implementation plan; certify implementation-ready |
| plan-verify | Plan audits: foundation, master, alignment, coverage (code→SPEC), brownfield |
| plan-repair | Remediate plan gaps; brownfield synthesis; mandatory re-verify |
| session-control | Session open/close; HANDOFF, NEXT; `context` read-only load; optional git |
| db-migration | Idempotent numbered SQL migration scripts |
| code-implementation | Iteration execution from NEXT.md |
| code-verify | Milestone/uncommitted/last audits |
| tauri-development | Tauri desktop: IPC security, shell/webview, Rust backend, events |
| code-repair | Fix verify/SPEC/migration findings |
| dev-stack | Isolated Docker Compose dev stack helper |
| process-router | Read-only process Q&A router |
| feature-spec | Author, review, amend feature SPECs |
| concept-run | Run MOD-01…MOD-07 concept prompts |
| project-bootstrap | Copy `.work/` skeleton, `.cursorrules`, stack doc from templates |
| docs | Create/manage project docs under `.work/docs/` |
| deploy-files | Fat-client deploy (vendored): full `.ai/` tree into target; no-overwrite; `update` rules-aware merge |
| deploy-basic | Thin-client bootstrap / `update`: re-sync `AGENT_OS_SOURCE` + merge local scaffold (skills resolve from source) |
| deploy-repo | Full repo deploy: clone (git mirror) or archive (snapshot) |
| project-query-setup | Optional tools-project API key + MCP registration + connectivity test |
| ai-director | Free-text orchestrator; routes to `.ai` skill chain; skill-gap detection |
| x-director | Cross-framework orchestrator (`.ai` + `.ai.ui` + `.ai.biz` + `.ai.soc`) |

**New skills:** add `.ai/skills/<id>/skill.md`; register above. Naming: `.ai/skills/README.md` § Naming protocol (`{domain}-{role}`, kebab-case).

